The original release of ''Dun Darach'' received critical acclaim, particularly for its graphics.<ref name=Crash1>{{cite magazine |magazine=[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]] |title=Reviews |pages=16–18 |date=July 1985 |issue=18 |url=https://archive.org/details/Crash_No._18_1985-07_Newsfield_GB/page/n15}}</ref><ref name=Amtix>{{cite magazine |magazine=[[Amtix]] |title=Reviews |page=7 |date=October 1985 |url=https://archive.org/details/amtix-magazine-00/page/n5}}</ref> The ZX Spectrum version was voted number 57 in the ''[[Your Sinclair]] Official Top 100 Games of All Time''.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Let the People Decide! The Results! |magazine=[[Your Sinclair]] |publisher=[[Dennis Publishing]] |page=11 |issue=93 |date=September 1993 |url=https://archive.org/stream/your-sinclair-93/YourSinclair_93_Sep_1993#page/n57/mode/2up}}</ref> Richard Price for ''Sinclair User'', while describing the game as "less abstract" as ''Tir Na Nog'', said it was more interesting and eventful than its predecessor.<ref name=SUser>{{cite magazine |magazine=[[Sinclair User]] |last=Price |first=Richard |title=Adventure |date=August 1985 |pages=92–94 |issue=41 |url=https://archive.org/details/sinclair-user-magazine-041/page/n91}}</ref> ''[[Computer And Video Games]]'' considered it a worthy successor to the first, calling it "entertaining".<ref name=CVG>{{cite magazine |magazine=[[Computer And Video Games]] |title=Reviews |page=28 |date=August 1985 |issue=46 |url=https://archive.org/details/ComputerAndVideoGamesIssue046Aug85/page/n27}}</ref> A reviewer for [[Crash (magazine)|''Crash'']] declared it an essential purchase for ZX Spectrum owners and saw it as a contender for game of the year.<ref name=Crash1/> Retrospective appraisals were less agreeable. ''[[Eurogamer]]'' contributor Peter Parrish offered an average score overall, dubbing it "mystifying".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/dun-darach-review |title=''Dun Darach'' |last=Parrish |first=Peter |work=[[Eurogamer]] |date=16 October 2007 |access-date=8 January 2020 |archive-date=4 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004220800/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/dun-darach-review |url-status=live}}</ref> Ian Marks from ''[[Retro Gamer]]'' compared it to ''Tir Na Nog'', saying both were fun to play but ''Dun Darach'' was not as good. Marks also noted the novelty of the graphics wore off.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.retrogamer.net/retro_games80/dun-darach/ |title=''Dun Darach'' |last=Marks |first=Ian |work=[[Retro Gamer]] |date=20 January 2009 |access-date=8 January 2020 |archive-date=20 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020061432/https://www.retrogamer.net/retro_games80/dun-darach/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

